Diagnostic description. Body length 11.9–23.1 mm ( 21.9 mm in the lectotype ), maximum body width 8.5– 11.9 mm ( 11.2 mm in the lectotype ). Pronotum orange in dorsal view (
Figs. 5–6
). Hypomeron medially orange in ventral view, dark metallic blue only along its posterior margin. Elytra brown to dark brown, without metallic luster; outline subrectangular; costae finer, less elevated (
Figs. 5–6
).

Male . Elytra laterally parallel and more narrow than in
N. brunnicollis
(
Fig. 5
). Metatibia only slightly bent. Male genital segment with longer spiculum gastrale in ventral view (
Fig. 43
). Aedeagus with median lobe distinctly shorter than slender, elongate parameres in ventral view (
Figs. 42
).

Distribution (
Fig. 63
). Endemic Taiwanese species (Portevin 1914 ,
Nishikawa 2014
).
